cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a model for sentence representation using variational self-attention. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as stance detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also employs variational inference, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses probabilistic distributions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also uses stochastic units, which is a common technique in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Finally, the paper uses attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category.
